HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100 da suka kamu da cutar
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan Sinawa da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau.
Fiye da mutane 820,000 ne cutar ta shafa a kasar Sin, in ji jami'ai.
Kimanin sabbin mutane 40,000 aka ruwaito a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan sun kasance masu yaduwa ta hanyar jima'i, sabanin waɗanda suka gabata.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yadu da sauri a wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin ta wajen karɓan jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin a wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau a kasar Sin ya karu da 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a China.
An dakatar da nuna luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Saboda tsattsauran ra'ayin kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mace.
Yawancin cututtuka da ke faruwa a cikin jima'i suna zuwa ne daga rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin irin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar, a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
